<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This has the appearance of a nearly glabrous prostrate form of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea campestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea campestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite variable in leaf shape but is always readily distinguished by the longer, narrower corolla, which reaches 6 cm, and the conspicuous pubescent indumentum of the inflorescence and corolla.
</paragraph>
